condition.narrative: Borrower shall prepare and furnish to the Association a Financial Monitoring Report, in form and substance satisfactory to theAssociation

Each Financial Statements shall cover the period of one Fiscal Year. The audited Financial Statements for each period shall befurnished to the Association not later than six months after the end of such period.

No later than 2 months after the Effective Date, the Recipient shall have recruited an independent agency with TORs,qualificationsand experience satisfactory to IDA for the purpose of independently collecting data & monitoring indicators for theProject
Not later than one month prior to the annual review, the Recipient shall furnish to IDA, for its comments, a progress report
The Borrower shall update the Procurement Plan and furnish it to the Association not later than 12 months after the date of thepreceding plan for IDA's approval
The Borrower shall update the Procurement Plan and furnish it to the Association not later than 12 months after the date of thepreceding plan for IDA's approval
The Borrower shall, not later than December 31 of each year, undertake, in conjunction with the Association and other interestedparties, an annual review of the Project.
The Recipient regularly collect, compile and submit to IDA, on a quarterly basis, reports on the status of compliance with theMedical Waste Management Plan
The Recipient shall comply with its obligations of repayment of ineligible expenditures incurred during the implementation of theoriginal project

The Recipient shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the Project & prepare Project Reports covering the period of onesemester,and shall be furnished to IDA not later than 2 months after the end of the period covered by such report.
The Recipient shall prepare and furnish to IDA not later than 45 days after the end of each calendar quarter, interim unauditedfinancial reports for the Project covering the quarter.

The Recipient shall prepare and furnish to the Association, not later than 45 days after the end of each calendar quarter, interimunaudited financial reports of the Project covering the quarter, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association.

The Recipient shall take all measures necessary on its part to regularly collect, compile, and submit to the Association, on aquarterly basis, reports on the status of compliance with the Medical Waste Management Plan.
The Recipient shall, not later than Dec. 31 of each year, undertake in conjonction with IDA an annual review of the projectfocusing on the project progress

The Recipient shall, not later than Sept. 30 of each year, submit to the IDA, for its review & approval, a proposed annual workprogram & budget for the forthcoming FY, except that, in the case of the period of time between the Effective Date and the end ofthe FY 2013, the proposed annual work program and budget shall be submitted to the Association not later than 30 days afterEffectiveness
The first FMR shall be furnished to IDA within 45 days after the end of the first calendar quarter after the Effective Date and 45days after each subsequent calandar quarter
furnish to IDA at least 6 mos. after end of FY: (A) certified copies of audits and b) the auditors'opinion
